children.text: At the summit of Mountaintop Express (#4). Grab breakfast or lunch with views of Sun Up Bowl and the Legendary Back Bowl's Gate.
Vail's iconic mountaintop venue at the top of Sourdough Express Lift #14 with views of the Legendary Back Bowls. Try out the signature Pork Green Chili and the Chicken Pasole Soup!
Two Elk Ski Patrol Station
Eagle's Nest Ski Patrol Station
At the bottom of Pete's Express (#39) providing lunch and snacks to those venturing far out into Pete's Bowl at Blue Sky Basin. No indoor seating.
Refuel at Vail Mountain's farther outpost. Enjoy snacks and beverages atop Blue Sky Basin at the summit of Skyline (#37) and Earl's (#38).
The 10th is Vail’s premier on-mountain full service restaurant, located atop Gondola One at Mid-Vail. Reservations required.
Still Smoking at 2 Miles High! Head up Wildwood Express Lift #3, Sun Down Express Lift #17 or the new Game Creek Express Lift #7 to get to Vail Mountain's specialty BBQ location.

Nourishing your legendary mountain adventures. Margie’s Haas breakfast is a tribute to the World War II local home cook, Margie Haas, who welcomed soldiers from the 10th Mountain Division into her home.
Welcome to where après begins. Capturing the revelry and passion for our mountains, Revel Lounge celebrates your day’s adventures with hand-crafted cocktails and Colorado-inspired cuisine.
Savor Colorado-crafted whiskey and spirits from our resort's lobby bar.
Positioned atop Eagle Bahn (#19), a fast casual restaurant with a full bar featuring art by Gray Malin.
The gateway to village après at the base of Gondola One! Ski right in for one of our many beers on tap and a delicious warm pretzel.

Cucina offers mountain-comfort cuisine with a laid back and family-friendly atmosphere. Known for its heart breakfast buffet before a day up the mountain, Cucina is also the perfect setting for unwinding after a day filled with Vail adventures. Cucina’s outdoor fire pit and recently renovated bar draw locals and visitors alike for its stellar family-friendly aprés-ski scene during the winter season. Cucina offers an unbeatable location in the heart of Vail Village.

Just steps from the Eagle Bahn Gondola, in the Arrabelle within Lionshead Village, the Tavern has a creative and delicious array of lunch and dinner selections. Try our quick service walk up bar with dining on the square and gastropub cuisine, or enjoy a reservations only a la carte dining experience on the mountain side and patio. An outdoor patio with breathtaking mountain views, the Tavern is the perfect spot after a day on the mountain!
Gourmet Coffee Shop and Bakery
Located at the top of Gondola One (#1), Mid-Vail offers spectacular views of the Gore Range and a variety of on-mountain lunch options.
Serving up lunch seven days a week atop the Eagle Bahn Gondola (#19) with iconic views of Mount of the Holy Cross and Game Creek Bowl.
At the summit of Mountaintop Express (#4). Grab breakfast or lunch with views of Sun Up Bowl and the Legendary Back Bowl's Gate.
Vail's newest grab and go café is located at the top of Eagle Bahn Gondola (#19) serving up warm coffee and sweet ice cream.
Crispy fried chicken served mountainside. Located at the bottom of Avanti Express (#2) it's the perfect location for a quick stop in-between runs.
